J Biol Chem. 1957 Oct;228(2):923-45. The bacterial oxidation of nicotinic acid.

Many nucleoside diphosphates (eight described) can act as acceptors. While many ribo- and deoxyribonucleoside triphosphates can act as donors, only ATP is chosen as a donor to minimize the number of total reactions.
